1
00:01:41,439 --> 00:01:42,120
Dr. Fang.

2
00:01:42,319 --> 00:01:43,319
Bed 15 is in ventricular fibrillation.

3
00:01:44,120 --> 00:01:45,200
Defibrillator. Bag-valve mask.

4
00:01:45,200 --> 00:01:46,159
Prepare for intubation.

5
00:01:46,159 --> 00:01:46,519
Come on.

6
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:48,439
One, two, three.

7
00:01:48,519 --> 00:01:49,840
Four, five, six.

8
00:01:49,920 --> 00:01:51,200
Seven, eight, nine.

9
00:01:51,239 --> 00:01:52,359
Ten, eleven, twelve.

10
00:01:54,680 --> 00:01:55,280
Turn on the defibrillator.

11
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:57,120
Unsynchronized, 200 joules.

12
00:01:58,760 --> 00:01:59,280
200 joules.

13
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:02,400
Check the rhythm again.

14
00:02:02,840 --> 00:02:03,480
V-fib confirmed.

15
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:04,480
Charge.

16
00:02:05,359 --> 00:02:05,920
Clear.

17
00:02:06,719 --> 00:02:07,159
Shock.

18
00:02:12,719 --> 00:02:13,280
Keep compressing.

19
00:02:13,919 --> 00:02:15,719
One, two, three, four.

20
00:02:15,759 --> 00:02:17,159
Five, six, seven.

21
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:18,719
Check the rhythm again.

22
00:02:25,599 --> 00:02:26,360
Sinus rhythm restored.

23
00:02:29,879 --> 00:02:30,439
Lu Dadong.

24
00:02:31,319 --> 00:02:32,039
Lu Dadong.

25
00:02:32,759 --> 00:02:33,759
Can you hear me?

26
00:02:33,759 --> 00:02:34,479
Lu Dadong.

27
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:36,800
Yes.

28
00:02:40,039 --> 00:02:41,080
How do you feel now?

29
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:45,039
Who... who hit me?

30
00:02:45,879 --> 00:02:46,639
It hurts.

31
00:02:48,639 --> 00:02:50,199
Defibrillation can be painful.

32
00:02:50,599 --> 00:02:51,680
It'll ease up in a moment.

33
00:02:52,280 --> 00:02:53,439
I think I saw...

34
00:02:54,159 --> 00:02:55,039
my great-grandma.

35
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:03,120
Liang Mei, come with me.

36
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,840
These are the only two treatment options for now.

37
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:12,680
Talk it over carefully.

38
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:30,960
Can I just take medicine?

39
00:03:31,319 --> 00:03:32,719
Your heart failure is severe.

40
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:34,280
Your heart function is very poor.

41
00:03:35,080 --> 00:03:36,039
Medication alone can't...

42
00:03:36,039 --> 00:03:36,960
restore it completely.

43
00:03:42,719 --> 00:03:43,639
Then I won't treat it.

44
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:46,199
Why not?

45
00:03:48,719 --> 00:03:49,360
Dr. Liang.

46
00:03:49,599 --> 00:03:50,400
Bed 10 is in ventricular fibrillation.

47
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:51,560
Crash cart. Defibrillator.

48
00:03:51,639 --> 00:03:52,960
Two, three, four.

49
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:53,360
Five.

50
00:03:53,439 --> 00:03:54,199
Six, seven.

51
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:55,080
Turn on the defibrillator.

52
00:03:55,759 --> 00:03:56,039
Okay.

53
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:57,000
Nineteen, twenty.

54
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:57,800
Unsynchronized, 200 joules.

55
00:03:58,159 --> 00:03:58,639
Charge.

56
00:03:59,360 --> 00:03:59,879
Clear.

57
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:00,759
Shock.

58
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:04,199
Resume compressions.

59
00:04:04,759 --> 00:04:06,400
One, two, three, four.

60
00:04:06,479 --> 00:04:07,759
Five, six.

61
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:15,360
Dadong.

62
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:18,079
If you refuse mechanical support,

63
00:04:18,319 --> 00:04:19,759
you're basically giving up treatment.

64
00:04:20,439 --> 00:04:21,240
Then I'll give up.

65
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:22,800
I give up.

66
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:27,639
Even if we spend all that money,

67
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:29,959
I still might not survive.

68
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:33,319
You will.

69
00:04:33,519 --> 00:04:34,720
Don't worry about the money.

70
00:04:34,879 --> 00:04:35,480
I have some.

71
00:04:35,839 --> 00:04:37,600
Haven't we saved up these past two years?

72
00:04:37,959 --> 00:04:38,839
I'm able-bodied.

73
00:04:38,839 --> 00:04:39,759
I can borrow money.

74
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:40,560
The house back home...

75
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:41,680
a lot of people have come to see it.

76
00:04:41,680 --> 00:04:42,480
No. No.

77
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:44,360
Xiaomei, we can't sell the house.

78
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:45,639
We can't sell it.

79
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,519
If you sell it, I'm leaving the hospital.

80
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:49,959
What are you doing?

81
00:04:50,519 --> 00:04:51,160
Don't move around.

82
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:51,600
Don't disconnect the equipment.

83
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:52,160
You can't move.

84
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:52,480
Dadong.

85
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:53,399
Dadong.

86
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:53,920
Don't.

87
00:04:54,040 --> 00:04:56,160
What are you doing?

88
00:04:56,399 --> 00:04:58,120
Listen to me, okay?

89
00:04:58,360 --> 00:04:59,319
You need treatment.

90
00:04:59,720 --> 00:05:00,959
You need treatment.

91
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:02,720
Listen to me.

92
00:05:02,839 --> 00:05:03,800
Liang Mei, listen.

93
00:05:04,279 --> 00:05:05,279
Don't get too worked up.

94
00:05:05,959 --> 00:05:06,560
How about this?

95
00:05:07,439 --> 00:05:08,480
Go outside and get some rest.

96
00:05:08,639 --> 00:05:09,639
We'll talk to him.

97
00:05:09,959 --> 00:05:10,399
All right?

98
00:05:12,319 --> 00:05:12,800
Beibei.

99
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:13,839
Take Liang Mei outside to rest.

100
00:05:13,839 --> 00:05:14,319
Okay, okay.

101
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:14,759
Let's go.

102
00:05:14,839 --> 00:05:15,399
We won't sell the house.

103
00:05:15,560 --> 00:05:16,319
Easy, Xiaomei.

104
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:24,240
Dadong.

105
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:26,680
Liang Mei has no family left.

106
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:28,360
You're all she has now.

107
00:05:28,839 --> 00:05:30,000
Can you really leave her behind?

108
00:05:37,199 --> 00:05:38,079
If I die,

109
00:05:40,199 --> 00:05:41,639
she'll still have the house.

110
00:05:42,879 --> 00:05:44,079
When she gets married someday,

111
00:05:45,160 --> 00:05:46,720
it can be her dowry.

112
00:05:47,279 --> 00:05:49,480
But if she sells the house

113
00:05:50,879 --> 00:05:52,319
and I still don't get better,

114
00:05:52,759 --> 00:05:53,720
the money will be gone too.

115
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:55,959
What will she have left?

116
00:05:58,120 --> 00:05:59,959
A box... a box of ashes.

117
00:06:00,759 --> 00:06:01,519
Don't get worked up.

118
00:06:01,519 --> 00:06:02,399
And a mountain of debt.

119
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:07,680
Dadong.

120
00:06:08,839 --> 00:06:09,800
No matter what,

121
00:06:10,759 --> 00:06:12,079
a life matters more than money.

122
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:16,319
Director Zhou.

123
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:19,240
For people like us,

124
00:06:20,639 --> 00:06:22,040
money is too hard to earn.

125
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:28,079
Money matters more than life.

126
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:31,079
Much more.

127
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:34,639
You big dummy.

128
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:38,120
Stop thinking about dying.

129
00:06:38,519 --> 00:06:39,600
To us,

130
00:06:39,879 --> 00:06:41,040
you're what matters most.

131
00:06:45,160 --> 00:06:46,240
Believe in yourself.

132
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:48,639
And believe in us.

133
00:06:49,759 --> 00:06:50,319
I'm tired.

134
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:54,920
I'm tired.

135
00:07:02,399 --> 00:07:03,360
These past two years in Guizhou,

136
00:07:03,920 --> 00:07:04,560
I've met many

137
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:05,399
families like theirs.

138
00:07:06,439 --> 00:07:07,480
Even after rural medical reimbursement,

139
00:07:07,839 --> 00:07:09,120
the financial burden is still heavy.

140
00:07:13,759 --> 00:07:14,720
I've been a doctor for so long.

141
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:17,720
Even when we can predict how an illness may progress,

142
00:07:18,519 --> 00:07:20,040
we still can't predict what a patient is thinking.

143
00:07:21,199 --> 00:07:22,040
It's not just that we can't predict

144
00:07:22,079 --> 00:07:23,040
a patient's thoughts.

145
00:07:23,839 --> 00:07:24,480
What do you mean?

146
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:30,560
The other day, Xiaorui suddenly told me

147
00:07:31,879 --> 00:07:32,800
that even if one day

148
00:07:33,279 --> 00:07:34,680
he needed a left ventricular assist device,

149
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:37,959
he still wouldn't want one.

150
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:41,319
He said he wants

151
00:07:41,319 --> 00:07:42,319
to live like a normal person.

152
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:51,759
What do you think?

153
00:07:58,800 --> 00:07:59,319
Xiao Wu.

154
00:07:59,759 --> 00:08:00,319
Director Zhou.

155
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:01,959
Are you free at noon?

156
00:08:02,199 --> 00:08:03,480
Experts from the provincial inspection team

157
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:04,600
are visiting the hospital.

158
00:08:04,720 --> 00:08:05,959
Director Song from the Health Commission

159
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:07,079
is leading the delegation personally.

160
00:08:07,439 --> 00:08:08,680
President Cui asked me to invite you

161
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:09,399
to lunch with them.

162
00:08:10,319 --> 00:08:11,000
Right now?

163
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:12,600
I have clinic this afternoon.

164
00:08:12,839 --> 00:08:14,800
It's nearby, right next to the Health Commission.

165
00:08:15,079 --> 00:08:15,920
Director Song specifically

166
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:17,040
asked about you this morning.

167
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:18,720
He's very interested in your congenital heart project.

168
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:19,680
All right.

169
00:08:19,959 --> 00:08:20,399
Okay.

170
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:23,959
It's fine. Go take care of it.

171
00:08:26,480 --> 00:08:27,000
We'll think of something together

172
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:27,959
about Xiaorui later.

173
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:30,040
For now, let's figure out how to get Lu Dadong

174
00:08:30,079 --> 00:08:30,800
to accept treatment.

175
00:08:35,360 --> 00:08:36,120
Time to eat, Xiaorui.

176
00:08:36,360 --> 00:08:37,399
Today I made your favorites:

177
00:08:37,519 --> 00:08:39,120
tomato and eggs, and celery with dried tofu.

178
00:08:39,759 --> 00:08:40,440
Did you add sugar?

179
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:41,799
No.

180
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:43,000
Don't worry.

181
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:51,080
Don't put everything away yet.

182
00:08:51,159 --> 00:08:51,679
Almost done.

183
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:54,120
What are you making?

184
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:56,200
A hair clip.

185
00:09:02,440 --> 00:09:02,840
Done.

186
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:03,879
How is it?

187
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:05,279
Pretty, right?

188
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:07,600
Who's it for?

189
00:09:08,399 --> 00:09:09,120
For Sister Xiaomei.

190
00:09:09,919 --> 00:09:10,759
Take it to her for me later.

191
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:12,639
Sure.

192
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:28,279
Xiaorui.

193
00:09:29,159 --> 00:09:30,200
Help me with something after lunch.

194
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:55,000
Brother Dongzi.

195
00:09:57,159 --> 00:09:58,039
I came to tell you

196
00:09:58,519 --> 00:09:59,159
I'm being discharged.

197
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:03,240
This...

198
00:10:05,399 --> 00:10:06,240
It's the hair clip

199
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:07,320
Sister Xiaomei said she liked last time.

200
00:10:07,720 --> 00:10:08,240
I finished it.

201
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:10,679
You have to put it on her yourself.

202
00:10:21,720 --> 00:10:22,440
Your wedding candy...

203
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:23,679
I ate it all.

204
00:10:24,720 --> 00:10:25,320
Now I'm waiting

205
00:10:25,360 --> 00:10:26,240
to see you in your wedding clothes

206
00:10:27,039 --> 00:10:27,960
and drink at your wedding banquet.

207
00:10:30,960 --> 00:10:31,279
Right.

208
00:10:31,759 --> 00:10:32,600
Didn't you say last time

209
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:33,360
that you two didn't have time

210
00:10:33,639 --> 00:10:34,559
to prepare wedding rings?

211
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:35,960
I used the wedding candy wrappers

212
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:37,399
to make two temporary ones.

213
00:10:47,639 --> 00:10:48,200
Do you remember?

214
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:52,360
The double-happiness character on the wrapper.

215
00:10:56,360 --> 00:10:57,360
I was in a rush,

216
00:10:57,720 --> 00:10:58,399
so they're a little rough.

217
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:24,759
Now...

218
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:26,799
Look at me now.

219
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,360
I can't give her anything.

220
00:11:31,039 --> 00:11:32,919
I'm only hurting Xiaomei.

221
00:11:34,320 --> 00:11:35,159
I've ruined her life.

222
00:11:37,360 --> 00:11:38,480
No.

223
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:39,759
When two people are together,

224
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:41,960
how could they keep score

225
00:11:42,039 --> 00:11:42,960
about who has hurt whom?

226
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:45,559
Out of all the people in the world,

227
00:11:46,360 --> 00:11:47,320
finding someone

228
00:11:47,320 --> 00:11:48,240
who truly loves you

229
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:49,440
and wants to spend a lifetime with you...

230
00:11:50,279 --> 00:11:51,120
If it were me,

231
00:11:54,120 --> 00:11:55,320
I couldn't bear to give that up either.

232
00:12:05,039 --> 00:12:06,159
I can't bear to either.

233
00:12:06,879 --> 00:12:08,000
But I'm scared.

234
00:12:10,360 --> 00:12:10,960
Director Lin.

235
00:12:12,879 --> 00:12:14,039
Only these past two days

236
00:12:14,080 --> 00:12:15,279
have I understood what illness I have.

237
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:17,480
I'm afraid of dying.

238
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:21,840
But I'm even more afraid of dragging Xiaomei down.

239
00:12:24,919 --> 00:12:25,519
Dadong.

240
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:27,600
You said you wanted

241
00:12:27,639 --> 00:12:28,759
to sell the house

242
00:12:28,840 --> 00:12:30,600
and leave the money to Xiaomei as a dowry.

243
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:33,120
Don't you think you're underestimating her?

244
00:12:34,080 --> 00:12:34,799
She's still so young

245
00:12:34,799 --> 00:12:35,720
and perfectly able to work.

246
00:12:36,080 --> 00:12:37,279
Do you really think she'll spend her whole life

247
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:38,799
living off the money from your house?

248
00:12:39,480 --> 00:12:40,320
For your treatment, we would use

249
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:41,039
ECMO.

250
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:42,360
after insurance reimbursement,

251
00:12:42,559 --> 00:12:43,360
will only cost you

252
00:12:43,399 --> 00:12:44,519
tens of thousands of yuan out of pocket.

253
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:47,000
Xiaomei can earn

254
00:12:47,039 --> 00:12:48,200
many times that amount in the future.

255
00:12:48,360 --> 00:12:49,200
So can you.

256
00:12:49,639 --> 00:12:50,240
But you,

257
00:12:50,240 --> 00:12:51,639
if you give up now,

258
00:12:51,960 --> 00:12:52,679
Xiaomei will spend the rest of her life

259
00:12:52,720 --> 00:12:54,039
thinking about you again and again,

260
00:12:54,279 --> 00:12:55,039
thinking about how you...

261
00:12:55,039 --> 00:12:56,320
You died just to save her tens of thousands of yuan.

262
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:56,919
You threw your life away.

263
00:12:57,399 --> 00:12:58,440
How do you expect her

264
00:12:58,480 --> 00:12:59,000
to go on after that?

265
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:01,600
Stop crying.

266
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:03,679
You're a grown man.

267
00:13:03,720 --> 00:13:04,960
What can't you get through?

268
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:06,960
Besides, you don't have to

269
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:07,840
carry this alone anymore.

270
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:09,440
Xiaomei is here.

271
00:13:10,919 --> 00:13:11,559
And so are we.

272
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:12,320
Exactly.

273
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:13,720
Brother Dongzi.

274
00:13:14,320 --> 00:13:14,799
I'm here too.

275
00:13:16,919 --> 00:13:17,840
Xiaomei's ring...

276
00:13:18,559 --> 00:13:19,759
you have to put it on her yourself.

277
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:24,879
You're going to get better.

278
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:27,200
Both of us will be fine.

279
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:28,799
We'll leave the hospital together

280
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:30,639
and never say goodbye to it again.

281
00:13:32,120 --> 00:13:32,559
Okay.

282
00:13:47,279 --> 00:13:48,600
Lu Dadong.

283
00:13:50,639 --> 00:13:52,120
Lu Dadong, you...

284
00:13:53,679 --> 00:13:55,519
you big idiot.

285
00:13:57,679 --> 00:13:59,639
I could kill you.

286
00:13:59,720 --> 00:14:02,559
How could you say something like that?

287
00:14:04,519 --> 00:14:05,320
I'm sorry.

288
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:08,399
Dadong.

289
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:13,039
Dadong.

290
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:15,759
I don't want you

291
00:14:15,799 --> 00:14:17,600
to prepare any dowry for me.

292
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:19,679
I want you.

293
00:14:21,639 --> 00:14:22,360
No matter

294
00:14:22,840 --> 00:14:24,000
what happens to you in the future,

295
00:14:25,519 --> 00:14:27,360
I'll face it with you.

296
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:38,960
Lin Yi.

297
00:14:41,120 --> 00:14:42,240
Why is it that when I'm sick,

298
00:14:42,679 --> 00:14:44,000
you can love me with all your heart

299
00:14:44,080 --> 00:14:45,039
and risk everything for me,

300
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:46,639
but when you're the one with a problem,

301
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:47,320
you won't let me

302
00:14:47,360 --> 00:14:49,120
love you the same way?

303
00:14:52,039 --> 00:14:52,960
No matter what happens,

304
00:14:53,639 --> 00:14:54,759
I'll face it with you.

305
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:26,399
Xiaomei.

306
00:15:27,919 --> 00:15:28,840
When I get better,

307
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:31,399
I'll get you a real gold one.

308
00:15:45,559 --> 00:15:45,960
Hello?

309
00:15:46,399 --> 00:15:47,759
Lu Dadong agreed to treatment.

310
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:49,320
If his condition worsens,

311
00:15:49,960 --> 00:15:50,679
he'll prioritize

312
00:15:50,720 --> 00:15:51,279
ECMO.

313
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:52,159
That's great.

314
00:15:52,639 --> 00:15:53,679
I'll have Zhang Zhen get ready.

315
00:16:00,799 --> 00:16:01,440
I'm back at the hospital.

316
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:02,399
Come to my office.

317
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:10,759
Director Sheng.

318
00:16:23,840 --> 00:16:25,320
A friend of mine brought

319
00:16:25,320 --> 00:16:26,480
these osmanthus cakes back from Hangzhou.

320
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:28,559
They're from an old, famous shop there.

321
00:16:28,799 --> 00:16:30,000
My friend waited in line for a long time

322
00:16:30,039 --> 00:16:30,840
before getting them.

323
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:33,039
I remember your wife is from Hangzhou,

324
00:16:33,120 --> 00:16:34,240
so I brought them over right away.

325
00:16:34,559 --> 00:16:35,759
Let her try them

326
00:16:35,799 --> 00:16:36,440
and see if they're authentic.

327
00:16:36,960 --> 00:16:37,480
Have some water.

328
00:16:38,559 --> 00:16:39,039
Thank you.

329
00:16:47,240 --> 00:16:48,960
After I left your office last time,

330
00:16:49,080 --> 00:16:49,840
I discussed it

331
00:16:49,879 --> 00:16:50,840
with my boss.

332
00:16:51,440 --> 00:16:53,039
Since it's a new product launch,

333
00:16:53,440 --> 00:16:54,879
in addition to manufacturer support,

334
00:16:54,919 --> 00:16:56,279
we should do something more ourselves.

335
00:16:56,679 --> 00:16:57,679
So now,

336
00:16:57,759 --> 00:16:59,399
we've come up with a preliminary plan.

337
00:16:59,919 --> 00:17:01,559
We'll organize

338
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:03,360
a cardiac surgery industry salon

339
00:17:03,799 --> 00:17:05,279
and invite

340
00:17:05,480 --> 00:17:06,400
clinical experts like you,

341
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:07,839
as well as our distribution partners,

342
00:17:07,880 --> 00:17:08,680
to attend together.

343
00:17:11,559 --> 00:17:12,359
That's a good thing.

344
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:14,839
Manager Ouyang.

345
00:17:15,599 --> 00:17:17,440
You've also been working closely

346
00:17:17,839 --> 00:17:19,200
with Cardiology lately, haven't you?

347
00:17:21,559 --> 00:17:22,759
It was indeed because of

348
00:17:22,799 --> 00:17:23,680
Professor Fang's surgery

349
00:17:23,759 --> 00:17:25,000
that we had some contact.

350
00:17:25,559 --> 00:17:26,960
But honestly,

351
00:17:27,079 --> 00:17:28,400
we'd wanted even earlier

352
00:17:28,400 --> 00:17:29,119
to establish contact

353
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:30,039
with you, Director Sheng,

354
00:17:30,079 --> 00:17:30,960
and explore a partnership.

355
00:17:31,319 --> 00:17:32,440
We just weren't

356
00:17:32,480 --> 00:17:33,480
fully prepared,

357
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:34,799
so we didn't dare pay you a visit.

358
00:17:35,359 --> 00:17:36,359
Things are different now.

359
00:17:36,440 --> 00:17:37,920
We have a new LVAD,

360
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:39,680
so we came to you with confidence.

361
00:17:42,799 --> 00:17:43,759
If it's a good product,

362
00:17:44,920 --> 00:17:45,599
of course we're willing

363
00:17:45,640 --> 00:17:46,720
to recommend it to patients.

364
00:17:47,799 --> 00:17:49,000
We have a patient recently

365
00:17:49,119 --> 00:17:50,359
who would be a good fit for it.

366
00:17:50,799 --> 00:17:52,319
But he was admitted by Cardiology,

367
00:17:52,680 --> 00:17:53,559
so it's not my call.

368
00:17:53,920 --> 00:17:56,240
If the patient himself is willing,

369
00:17:57,720 --> 00:17:58,680
I have no objection.

370
00:18:01,079 --> 00:18:01,880
Thank you, Director Sheng.

371
00:18:02,720 --> 00:18:04,079
I won't keep you. I'll let you work.

372
00:18:04,240 --> 00:18:04,920
I'll be going.

373
00:18:26,839 --> 00:18:27,240
Come in.

374
00:18:29,519 --> 00:18:29,839
Director.

375
00:18:30,640 --> 00:18:31,599
The consent form

376
00:18:31,640 --> 00:18:32,200
for putting Lu Dadong on ECMO

377
00:18:32,240 --> 00:18:32,920
has already been signed

378
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:34,000
by Liang Mei.

379
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:34,920
Dr. Fang

380
00:18:34,960 --> 00:18:36,440
has also been maintaining him on medication.

381
00:18:36,720 --> 00:18:37,920
Have Dr. Qiao prepare.

382
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:39,400
If his condition deteriorates,

383
00:18:39,480 --> 00:18:40,519
put him on ECMO immediately.

384
00:18:40,960 --> 00:18:41,319
Understood.

385
00:18:42,279 --> 00:18:43,400
I've also finished

386
00:18:43,440 --> 00:18:44,279
the supplier list you asked for.

387
00:18:44,480 --> 00:18:45,279
It's ready.

388
00:18:50,720 --> 00:18:51,240
Recently,

389
00:18:51,559 --> 00:18:52,880
have the team leaders in our department

390
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:54,480
given any feedback on Mai'anpei?

391
00:18:55,279 --> 00:18:57,039
Their feedback on the product

392
00:18:57,039 --> 00:18:57,640
has been pretty good.

393
00:18:57,920 --> 00:18:59,480
Ouyang Da, who's in charge, is also very proactive.

394
00:18:59,960 --> 00:19:00,640
Whenever

395
00:19:00,680 --> 00:19:02,000
we need anything,

396
00:19:02,119 --> 00:19:03,200
she responds very quickly.

397
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:04,480
Director.

398
00:19:04,960 --> 00:19:06,079
I heard Ouyang Da

399
00:19:06,119 --> 00:19:07,160
used to be a doctor too.

400
00:19:07,599 --> 00:19:08,400
So when it comes to product

401
00:19:08,440 --> 00:19:09,640
information and support,

402
00:19:09,720 --> 00:19:11,279
she's extremely accurate and thorough.

403
00:19:12,240 --> 00:19:13,079
You really do love gossip.

404
00:19:13,640 --> 00:19:14,440
That's just what I heard.

405
00:19:15,039 --> 00:19:16,319
Have you heard whether Cardiac Surgery

406
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:18,319
has started working with Mai'anpei?

407
00:19:19,359 --> 00:19:20,880
I don't think so.

408
00:19:24,079 --> 00:19:25,880
But... I think I heard Dr. Qiao

409
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:26,799
mention it once.

410
00:19:26,960 --> 00:19:27,799
He said Director Sheng seemed to be

411
00:19:27,839 --> 00:19:28,960
in contact with their company

412
00:19:29,119 --> 00:19:30,519
about an LVAD product.

413
00:19:48,920 --> 00:19:50,519
The one in pink.

414
00:19:52,839 --> 00:19:53,400
Thanks, ma'am.

415
00:19:53,720 --> 00:19:54,079
No problem.

416
00:19:59,720 --> 00:20:00,680
A patient's condition

417
00:20:00,720 --> 00:20:01,559
and whether a product suits them

418
00:20:01,640 --> 00:20:02,799
are private medical information.

419
00:20:03,839 --> 00:20:04,400
From now on,

420
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:05,480
stay away from my patients and their families.

421
00:20:05,480 --> 00:20:06,039
Keep your distance.

422
00:20:37,359 --> 00:20:37,839
Where are you?

423
00:20:37,880 --> 00:20:38,240
Second Aunt.

424
00:20:38,440 --> 00:20:39,119
Over here. Here.

425
00:20:39,319 --> 00:20:39,799
Xiaomei.

426
00:20:40,960 --> 00:20:41,440
Xiaomei.

427
00:20:45,559 --> 00:20:45,880
Auntie.

428
00:20:46,319 --> 00:20:46,799
Come here.

429
00:20:46,960 --> 00:20:47,680
Third Uncle. Eldest Uncle.

430
00:20:48,519 --> 00:20:49,359
Why are you all here?

431
00:20:53,799 --> 00:20:54,680
The doctor said

432
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:56,599
they'll start with ECMO

433
00:20:56,920 --> 00:20:58,160
and use medication alongside it.

434
00:20:58,319 --> 00:20:59,359
It should work.

435
00:21:00,240 --> 00:21:01,240
If it doesn't,

436
00:21:01,279 --> 00:21:02,680
there'll still be time

437
00:21:02,720 --> 00:21:03,359
to put him on an LVAD.

438
00:21:04,880 --> 00:21:06,240
Is this about money or what?

439
00:21:06,720 --> 00:21:08,000
Why not use the best option right away?

440
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:09,000
Exactly.

441
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:10,279
You've got a car but won't drive it,

442
00:21:10,319 --> 00:21:11,480
and you're riding a bicycle instead.

443
00:21:11,559 --> 00:21:12,519
That won't do.

444
00:21:12,599 --> 00:21:13,720
What if treatment gets delayed?

445
00:21:16,440 --> 00:21:17,319
That's what the doctor said.

446
00:21:17,880 --> 00:21:18,599
I'm following the doctor's advice.

447
00:21:19,160 --> 00:21:20,119
Did you tell the doctor

448
00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:20,839
you couldn't afford it?

449
00:21:21,319 --> 00:21:22,640
Were they afraid you couldn't pay,

450
00:21:22,839 --> 00:21:23,519
so they wouldn't give our Dadong

451
00:21:23,559 --> 00:21:24,319
the best treatment?

452
00:21:24,920 --> 00:21:25,839
I didn't.

453
00:21:25,960 --> 00:21:26,799
Let me tell you.

454
00:21:27,480 --> 00:21:28,599
That apartment in the county

455
00:21:28,839 --> 00:21:29,599
was specifically left to Dadong

456
00:21:29,680 --> 00:21:30,720
by his grandfather.

457
00:21:30,880 --> 00:21:32,240
That property will always belong to the Lu family.

458
00:21:32,599 --> 00:21:33,720
You saw Dadong was seriously ill

459
00:21:33,759 --> 00:21:35,160
and rushed to register the marriage.

460
00:21:35,400 --> 00:21:35,960
Don't think we don't know

461
00:21:35,960 --> 00:21:36,640
what you're really after.

462
00:21:40,640 --> 00:21:41,319
What am I after?

463
00:21:43,160 --> 00:21:43,559
Third Uncle,

464
00:21:43,559 --> 00:21:44,759
how could you say that about me?

465
00:21:45,240 --> 00:21:46,119
I married Dadong

466
00:21:46,160 --> 00:21:47,359
not for that apartment.

467
00:21:47,720 --> 00:21:48,920
If he needs the money for treatment,

468
00:21:49,440 --> 00:21:50,200
I'll sell it immediately.

469
00:21:50,240 --> 00:21:51,319
I'll list it tomorrow.

470
00:21:51,680 --> 00:21:52,359
Mind how you speak to your elders.

471
00:21:52,400 --> 00:21:53,640
Show some respect.

472
00:21:54,440 --> 00:21:55,279
Your third uncle

473
00:21:55,279 --> 00:21:56,839
didn't mean it like that.

474
00:21:57,160 --> 00:21:57,680
We all know

475
00:21:57,680 --> 00:21:59,119
you're a good girl.

476
00:21:59,559 --> 00:22:00,400
Otherwise Dadong

477
00:22:00,480 --> 00:22:01,880
wouldn't have chosen you, right?

478
00:22:02,920 --> 00:22:04,160
But back to the point,

479
00:22:04,359 --> 00:22:05,759
you're here taking care of Dadong.

480
00:22:06,440 --> 00:22:07,160
You don't have time

481
00:22:07,160 --> 00:22:08,200
to run around handling everything.

482
00:22:08,480 --> 00:22:09,119
So why don't you

483
00:22:09,160 --> 00:22:11,000
leave the deed and the keys

484
00:22:11,119 --> 00:22:12,000
with me?

485
00:22:16,480 --> 00:22:18,200
Sign this authorization letter.

486
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:20,000
We'll take it to a real estate agency

487
00:22:20,039 --> 00:22:20,880
and list the property.

488
00:22:21,119 --> 00:22:22,599
We can even negotiate a better price for you.

489
00:22:23,160 --> 00:22:24,519
Come on. Sign here.

490
00:22:24,880 --> 00:22:25,160
Here.

491
00:22:25,559 --> 00:22:26,440
Just sign here.

492
00:22:29,799 --> 00:22:30,680
If you refuse,

493
00:22:30,880 --> 00:22:31,559
then we'll have no choice

494
00:22:31,559 --> 00:22:32,519
but to discharge Dadong

495
00:22:33,079 --> 00:22:33,839
and take him back home.

496
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:36,359
How can he leave? He can't be discharged.

497
00:22:36,599 --> 00:22:37,519
Stop making trouble.

498
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:38,960
His condition can only be treated

499
00:22:38,960 --> 00:22:40,200
in a major city.

500
00:22:40,319 --> 00:22:41,799
Let me make this clear.

501
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:43,000
In the Lu family,

502
00:22:43,240 --> 00:22:45,319
whether it's the man or the property,

503
00:22:45,359 --> 00:22:46,759
it belongs to the Lu family.

504
00:22:47,039 --> 00:22:48,119
Eldest Uncle, I'm begging you.

505
00:22:48,160 --> 00:22:49,400
Please leave.

506
00:22:49,440 --> 00:22:51,079
Bring out the property deed.

507
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:52,079
Listen to your second aunt.

508
00:22:52,079 --> 00:22:53,319
We're trying to save Dadong too.

509
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:54,000
Liang Mei.

510
00:22:55,200 --> 00:22:56,559
Liang Mei, I've been looking everywhere for you.

511
00:22:56,640 --> 00:22:58,119
Dr. Zhang Zhen said we need to make a payment.

512
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:00,279
The hospital bill hasn't been paid for days.

513
00:23:00,720 --> 00:23:01,279
Didn't you know?

514
00:23:03,960 --> 00:23:04,359
Let's go.

515
00:23:04,599 --> 00:23:05,000
Okay.

516
00:23:06,400 --> 00:23:07,559
Xiaomei, don't leave.

517
00:23:07,640 --> 00:23:09,000
We're not finished talking.

518
00:23:09,960 --> 00:23:10,960
Dadong's family is here.

519
00:23:11,200 --> 00:23:12,200
Isn't that perfect?

520
00:23:12,759 --> 00:23:13,480
You brought money, right?

521
00:23:13,680 --> 00:23:14,839
Pay the medical bill.

522
00:23:15,119 --> 00:23:15,440
Let's go.

523
00:23:17,880 --> 00:23:18,279
Well...

524
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:20,920
X-Xiaomei is going

525
00:23:21,079 --> 00:23:21,680
to make the payment.

526
00:23:21,920 --> 00:23:22,960
We'll come see you in a couple of days.

527
00:23:25,240 --> 00:23:26,000
They're not relatives?

528
00:23:29,720 --> 00:23:31,039
Don't worry. They didn't follow us.

529
00:23:33,599 --> 00:23:34,359
Thank you.

530
00:23:35,119 --> 00:23:35,680
How did you know

531
00:23:35,680 --> 00:23:36,720
my name?

532
00:23:37,720 --> 00:23:38,799
I work in medical devices.

533
00:23:39,039 --> 00:23:40,519
I'm around this building a lot.

534
00:23:41,160 --> 00:23:42,759
I know many patients

535
00:23:42,839 --> 00:23:44,279
and family members in Cardiology.

536
00:23:44,680 --> 00:23:45,640
Actually, I know a little

537
00:23:45,680 --> 00:23:46,759
about your situation too.

538
00:23:48,359 --> 00:23:49,319
My name is Ouyang Da.

539
00:23:51,440 --> 00:23:52,680
A medical device company?

540
00:23:53,759 --> 00:23:54,359
We...

541
00:23:54,440 --> 00:23:55,680
provide the machines and equipment

542
00:23:55,799 --> 00:23:56,839
used on patients in the hospital.

543
00:23:57,559 --> 00:23:59,000
We provide products and technical support

544
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:00,559
to hospitals and doctors.

545
00:24:04,599 --> 00:24:06,039
Thank you for today.

546
00:24:06,720 --> 00:24:07,440
You really helped me.

547
00:24:08,839 --> 00:24:09,599
I just couldn't stand seeing

548
00:24:09,640 --> 00:24:11,039
them bully a young woman like you.

549
00:24:11,519 --> 00:24:12,519
Whatever you do, don't sign

550
00:24:12,519 --> 00:24:13,799
any contracts or papers they bring you.

551
00:24:14,119 --> 00:24:15,119
They're up to no good.

552
00:24:15,720 --> 00:24:17,039
I've seen this many times.

553
00:24:21,480 --> 00:24:23,039
They never came before.

554
00:24:24,079 --> 00:24:25,880
If anything happened to Dadong and me,

555
00:24:26,359 --> 00:24:27,640
we couldn't count on them.

556
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:29,240
We handled everything ourselves.

557
00:24:30,599 --> 00:24:31,079
Today they said

558
00:24:31,079 --> 00:24:32,279
they came to see Dadong,

559
00:24:32,839 --> 00:24:34,200
but they didn't even bring a bag of fruit.

560
00:24:35,640 --> 00:24:36,240
I know.

561
00:24:36,960 --> 00:24:38,440
They're only here for the apartment.

562
00:24:40,319 --> 00:24:42,000
You understand exactly what's going on.

563
00:24:42,319 --> 00:24:42,839
That's good.

564
00:24:43,920 --> 00:24:44,920
Taking care of a patient

565
00:24:44,920 --> 00:24:45,799
must be exhausting.

566
00:24:46,440 --> 00:24:47,160
Get plenty of rest.

567
00:24:47,640 --> 00:24:48,640
And don't forget to take care of yourself.

568
00:24:49,079 --> 00:24:49,640
I'll get going.

569
00:24:49,799 --> 00:24:50,359
Okay. Thank you.

570
00:24:52,519 --> 00:24:52,960
Ma'am.

571
00:24:56,279 --> 00:24:57,400
Can I ask you something?

572
00:24:57,720 --> 00:24:58,160
What is it?

573
00:24:59,400 --> 00:25:00,839
You work for a device company.

574
00:25:01,519 --> 00:25:02,200
Then you must know

575
00:25:02,240 --> 00:25:03,079
about LVADs.

576
00:25:09,359 --> 00:25:10,640
Is the difference

577
00:25:10,640 --> 00:25:11,880
between an LVAD and ECMO

578
00:25:12,240 --> 00:25:13,559
really like one is riding a bicycle

579
00:25:13,599 --> 00:25:14,680
and the other is driving a car?

580
00:25:27,640 --> 00:25:29,000
I've arranged everything in Hainan.

581
00:25:29,119 --> 00:25:29,440
When you arrive,

582
00:25:29,440 --> 00:25:30,720
just contact Professor Zhang.

583
00:25:31,079 --> 00:25:31,559
No problem.

584
00:25:31,799 --> 00:25:32,240
Xiao Lin.

585
00:25:34,720 --> 00:25:35,680
Aren't you flying today?

586
00:25:35,920 --> 00:25:36,920
Yes, this afternoon.

587
00:25:37,039 --> 00:25:37,720
I'm going on rounds first.

588
00:25:38,039 --> 00:25:38,960
Take these two days off

589
00:25:39,039 --> 00:25:39,839
and spend time with Xiaorui.

590
00:25:40,119 --> 00:25:41,119
Don't worry about your patients.

591
00:25:41,160 --> 00:25:42,160
I've arranged everything for you.

592
00:25:43,079 --> 00:25:43,519
Thank you, Director.

593
00:25:43,759 --> 00:25:44,440
I'll go on rounds then.

594
00:25:49,240 --> 00:25:49,920
Director Sheng.

595
00:25:53,319 --> 00:25:54,200
Did you look at

596
00:25:54,240 --> 00:25:55,640
the joint clinic schedule I sent you?

597
00:25:55,960 --> 00:25:56,559
Have you looked at it?

598
00:25:56,720 --> 00:25:57,519
Any thoughts?

599
00:25:58,160 --> 00:25:59,880
The joint clinic is a good idea.

600
00:26:00,440 --> 00:26:01,799
But won't it

601
00:26:01,839 --> 00:26:02,519
be rather inefficient?

602
00:26:03,079 --> 00:26:03,559
Look,

603
00:26:04,079 --> 00:26:05,039
every doctor

604
00:26:05,279 --> 00:26:06,920
in both our departments is exceptional.

605
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:07,720
Forcing everyone to work together...

606
00:26:07,880 --> 00:26:09,039
isn't that a waste of resources?

607
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:11,400
With proper scheduling,

608
00:26:11,640 --> 00:26:13,039
our strengths can complement each other.

609
00:26:13,680 --> 00:26:15,039
Exactly. Proper scheduling.

610
00:26:16,759 --> 00:26:17,240
But...

611
00:26:17,759 --> 00:26:18,240
look.

612
00:26:18,960 --> 00:26:20,240
Lin Yi is already so busy.

613
00:26:20,359 --> 00:26:21,079
If he's away,

614
00:26:21,279 --> 00:26:22,240
does that mean Director Zhou

615
00:26:22,359 --> 00:26:23,160
won't hold clinic either?

616
00:26:37,039 --> 00:26:37,480
Hello?

617
00:26:37,720 --> 00:26:38,160
Brother.

618
00:26:38,599 --> 00:26:39,680
Lu Dadong isn't doing well.

619
00:26:39,839 --> 00:26:41,240
His blood pressure and oxygen saturation are lower.

620
00:26:41,279 --> 00:26:42,000
We're struggling to stabilize him.

621
00:26:42,359 --> 00:26:43,200
We'd already agreed

622
00:26:43,200 --> 00:26:43,960
that if he worsened, we'd start

623
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:44,680
ECMO.

624
00:26:45,039 --> 00:26:45,680
But now Liang Mei

625
00:26:45,680 --> 00:26:46,720
has suddenly changed her mind.

626
00:26:47,400 --> 00:26:47,839
What?

627
00:26:52,039 --> 00:26:52,559
Director Zhou.

628
00:26:53,279 --> 00:26:53,799
Dr. Fang.

629
00:26:54,319 --> 00:26:55,119
I'm sorry. I...

630
00:26:55,759 --> 00:26:56,759
I just want to make sure

631
00:26:56,839 --> 00:26:58,400
which treatment is best.

632
00:26:58,880 --> 00:26:59,720
You don't need

633
00:26:59,759 --> 00:27:00,759
to worry about the money for me.

634
00:27:00,920 --> 00:27:02,319
I'll find a way.

635
00:27:03,240 --> 00:27:04,559
If what they said is true,

636
00:27:05,359 --> 00:27:07,039
and an LVAD is better for Dadong,

637
00:27:07,240 --> 00:27:08,720
then give him the best option.

638
00:27:09,039 --> 00:27:09,839
I'll find a way to pay.

639
00:27:09,880 --> 00:27:10,519
Who told you

640
00:27:10,519 --> 00:27:11,680
an LVAD was better?

641
00:27:14,880 --> 00:27:15,960
I... I wanted to ask.

642
00:27:16,279 --> 00:27:17,000
Is the difference

643
00:27:17,079 --> 00:27:18,400
between an LVAD and ECMO

644
00:27:18,720 --> 00:27:19,960
really like one is riding a bicycle

645
00:27:20,039 --> 00:27:21,240
and the other is driving a car?

646
00:27:27,400 --> 00:27:28,480
You can't generalize like that.

647
00:27:29,039 --> 00:27:29,599
ECMO

648
00:27:29,599 --> 00:27:30,400
and an LVAD

649
00:27:30,519 --> 00:27:31,559
each serve different purposes.

650
00:27:32,359 --> 00:27:33,880
Director Zhou has his own clinical judgment.

651
00:27:34,599 --> 00:27:35,440
I think...

652
00:27:37,279 --> 00:27:38,599
maybe he considered

653
00:27:39,400 --> 00:27:40,920
your financial situation.

654
00:27:42,319 --> 00:27:44,240
After all, an LVAD is very expensive.

655
00:27:44,839 --> 00:27:45,400
ECMO

656
00:27:45,640 --> 00:27:46,400
is covered by medical insurance,

657
00:27:46,599 --> 00:27:47,759
which can save you a lot of money.

658
00:27:49,680 --> 00:27:50,279
If Director Zhou

659
00:27:50,279 --> 00:27:51,480
made this decision

660
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:52,440
because of our finances

661
00:27:52,440 --> 00:27:52,960
and chose ECMO,

662
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:53,960
then that won't do.

663
00:27:54,359 --> 00:27:55,599
I just want to save Dadong.

664
00:27:55,640 --> 00:27:56,519
As long as it can save him,

665
00:27:56,880 --> 00:27:57,799
I'll borrow money,

666
00:27:57,960 --> 00:27:58,480
sell the house,

667
00:27:58,799 --> 00:27:59,759
do whatever it takes.

668
00:27:59,799 --> 00:28:01,079
I just want him alive.

669
00:28:05,160 --> 00:28:06,039
Objectively speaking,

670
00:28:06,720 --> 00:28:07,799
for end-stage patients

671
00:28:07,799 --> 00:28:08,799
like Dadong,

672
00:28:09,640 --> 00:28:11,039
an LVAD is indeed

673
00:28:11,519 --> 00:28:13,319
a more effective

674
00:28:13,359 --> 00:28:14,920
and more common bridge therapy.

675
00:28:17,319 --> 00:28:18,720
With the newer generation of devices,

676
00:28:18,920 --> 00:28:19,799
many patients

677
00:28:19,799 --> 00:28:20,920
can even use them for life.

678
00:28:22,119 --> 00:28:23,839
After all, with a heart transplant,

679
00:28:24,039 --> 00:28:25,400
it takes time to wait for a donor.

680
00:28:26,119 --> 00:28:27,240
And there are also issues

681
00:28:27,599 --> 00:28:28,799
like matching and contraindications.

682
00:28:29,279 --> 00:28:30,079
Not everyone

683
00:28:30,200 --> 00:28:31,519
is eligible for the surgery.

684
00:28:31,799 --> 00:28:32,680
An LVAD

685
00:28:33,400 --> 00:28:33,839
is expensive,

686
00:28:34,200 --> 00:28:35,200
but there's a reason for the price.

687
00:28:36,319 --> 00:28:38,279
Manager Ouyang has been very kind to me.

688
00:28:39,240 --> 00:28:41,200
When Dadong's relatives pressured me,

689
00:28:42,480 --> 00:28:44,000
she was the one who helped me out.

690
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:46,519
Xiaomei.

691
00:28:48,200 --> 00:28:49,880
I can't guarantee anything,

692
00:28:50,240 --> 00:28:51,640
but as Dadong's doctor,

693
00:28:53,200 --> 00:28:54,039
I still believe

694
00:28:54,279 --> 00:28:55,720
that at this stage, ECMO

695
00:28:55,720 --> 00:28:56,799
combined with medication

696
00:28:57,720 --> 00:28:58,559
is the better option

697
00:28:58,599 --> 00:28:59,960
for the two of you.

698
00:29:02,839 --> 00:29:04,400
But if you have other thoughts,

699
00:29:04,920 --> 00:29:06,200
we'll naturally respect them.

700
00:29:09,480 --> 00:29:10,440
Dadong is still young.

701
00:29:11,559 --> 00:29:13,440
In the long run, a heart transplant

702
00:29:13,759 --> 00:29:14,960
is more suitable for him.

703
00:29:15,839 --> 00:29:16,680
But a transplant

704
00:29:17,359 --> 00:29:18,279
is extremely expensive.

705
00:29:18,640 --> 00:29:20,119
If you spend all your money now,

706
00:29:21,480 --> 00:29:23,119
what will you do

707
00:29:24,440 --> 00:29:25,799
when a donor heart finally becomes available?

708
00:29:33,359 --> 00:29:33,920
Yes.

709
00:29:38,319 --> 00:29:39,559
I hadn't thought that far ahead.

710
00:29:40,440 --> 00:29:41,599
I'm sorry, Director Zhou.

711
00:29:43,359 --> 00:29:44,599
It's not that I don't trust you.

712
00:29:44,599 --> 00:29:45,240
I... I...

713
00:29:45,640 --> 00:29:46,880
I truly didn't know what to do.

714
00:29:47,880 --> 00:29:48,960
It wasn't just Manager Ouyang.

715
00:29:49,640 --> 00:29:50,720
Dadong's relatives

716
00:29:50,799 --> 00:29:52,200
also said ECMO was no good.

717
00:29:52,720 --> 00:29:53,400
They even said they'd

718
00:29:53,599 --> 00:29:55,000
take Dadong back home for treatment.

719
00:29:55,160 --> 00:29:56,680
I panicked.

720
00:29:57,000 --> 00:29:57,920
Don't panic.

721
00:29:58,160 --> 00:29:59,880
You and Dadong are legally married.

722
00:30:00,160 --> 00:30:01,519
When it comes to choosing his treatment,

723
00:30:01,559 --> 00:30:02,920
you two have the primary right to decide.

724
00:30:03,160 --> 00:30:04,440
If you don't agree,

725
00:30:04,680 --> 00:30:06,079
no one can take Dadong away.

726
00:30:11,000 --> 00:30:12,000
Write down this number.

727
00:30:12,279 --> 00:30:13,240
This is Attorney Chen,

728
00:30:13,519 --> 00:30:14,519
a good friend of mine.

729
00:30:15,240 --> 00:30:16,000
If you have any

730
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:17,119
questions about disposing of marital property

731
00:30:17,240 --> 00:30:18,200
or signing an authorization,

732
00:30:18,279 --> 00:30:19,400
or any related legal issues,

733
00:30:19,640 --> 00:30:20,559
you can ask her.

734
00:30:20,920 --> 00:30:22,160
I'll let her know in advance.

735
00:30:22,279 --> 00:30:22,720
Okay.

736
00:30:33,160 --> 00:30:34,559
Thank you, Director Zhou.

737
00:30:35,839 --> 00:30:36,759
Thank you, Dr. Fang.

738
00:30:38,359 --> 00:30:39,279
You always put

739
00:30:39,319 --> 00:30:40,400
Dadong and me first.

740
00:30:43,759 --> 00:30:44,480
I'll follow your advice.

741
00:30:59,240 --> 00:30:59,640
Xiaomei.

742
00:31:00,240 --> 00:31:01,119
Take this money.

743
00:31:01,599 --> 00:31:02,200
Sis,

744
00:31:02,519 --> 00:31:03,119
I can't take it.

745
00:31:03,160 --> 00:31:03,680
Xiaomei.

746
00:31:04,079 --> 00:31:05,680
We all pooled this together for you.

747
00:31:05,839 --> 00:31:06,559
Take it.

748
00:31:06,799 --> 00:31:07,680
It's not much.

749
00:31:08,079 --> 00:31:08,599
Xiaomei.

750
00:31:09,240 --> 00:31:10,039
Listen to me.

751
00:31:10,359 --> 00:31:11,240
Take the money.

752
00:31:11,279 --> 00:31:12,720
There are so many expenses at the hospital.

753
00:31:12,880 --> 00:31:14,200
We can't help in any other way.

754
00:31:14,680 --> 00:31:15,119
Take it.

755
00:31:15,839 --> 00:31:16,480
Use it for emergencies.

756
00:31:17,039 --> 00:31:17,440
Right.

757
00:31:17,799 --> 00:31:18,279
Okay?

758
00:31:19,240 --> 00:31:20,000
Thank you.

759
00:31:21,359 --> 00:31:21,920
Thank you.

760
00:31:25,400 --> 00:31:26,319
I'll take the money.

761
00:31:27,799 --> 00:31:28,519
I promise I'll

762
00:31:28,559 --> 00:31:29,279
pay you all back someday.

763
00:31:30,440 --> 00:31:31,599
Don't worry about paying us back.

764
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:33,599
Getting Dongzi treated is what matters now.

765
00:31:37,640 --> 00:31:38,279
Here, Xiaomei.

766
00:31:39,279 --> 00:31:40,119
Take this too.

767
00:31:41,279 --> 00:31:42,079
Sis,

768
00:31:42,599 --> 00:31:44,200
I really can't accept this.

769
00:31:44,319 --> 00:31:45,759
I really can't.

770
00:31:45,839 --> 00:31:46,240
Xiaomei.

771
00:31:46,480 --> 00:31:47,279
Listen to me.

772
00:31:47,480 --> 00:31:48,759
You can't refuse. It's hollow.

773
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:49,960
It's hollow.

774
00:31:50,319 --> 00:31:51,240
It isn't worth much.

775
00:31:53,279 --> 00:31:54,440
The ring Dongzi gave you

776
00:31:54,680 --> 00:31:55,279
is beautiful.

777
00:31:56,039 --> 00:31:57,480
But what bride

778
00:31:57,680 --> 00:31:58,839
doesn't have a piece of gold jewelry?

779
00:31:59,559 --> 00:32:00,000
Exactly.

780
00:32:01,759 --> 00:32:02,960
And you don't have family on your side...

781
00:32:03,839 --> 00:32:04,640
The few of us

782
00:32:05,160 --> 00:32:06,200
are your family now.

783
00:32:11,440 --> 00:32:11,799
There.

784
00:32:16,240 --> 00:32:16,880
Does it look good?

785
00:32:22,599 --> 00:32:23,599
The doctors said

786
00:32:24,359 --> 00:32:25,640
you'll recover in a few days.

787
00:32:26,440 --> 00:32:27,079
Don't be afraid.

788
00:32:28,000 --> 00:32:29,000
I'll wait outside for you.

789
00:32:29,160 --> 00:32:29,880
I'm not going anywhere.

790
00:32:33,640 --> 00:32:34,079
I...

791
00:32:35,599 --> 00:32:37,839
If I don't wake up,

792
00:32:39,839 --> 00:32:41,640
don't wait for me.

793
00:32:55,839 --> 00:32:56,240
Fine.

794
00:32:57,000 --> 00:32:57,680
I won't wait.

795
00:32:59,039 --> 00:33:00,279
If you don't wake up,

796
00:33:00,759 --> 00:33:02,119
I'll take our house

797
00:33:02,559 --> 00:33:03,799
and marry a good man.

798
00:33:04,839 --> 00:33:05,680
I'll find someone tall,

799
00:33:06,160 --> 00:33:06,640
handsome,

800
00:33:07,240 --> 00:33:08,480
who buys me a big diamond ring

801
00:33:08,680 --> 00:33:09,319
and does what I say.

802
00:33:10,039 --> 00:33:10,799
Not like you.

803
00:33:11,400 --> 00:33:13,319
Dark, ugly, and always making me mad.

804
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:22,559
Then...

805
00:33:24,240 --> 00:33:26,640
when you visit my grave,

806
00:33:27,440 --> 00:33:28,519
don't bring him.

807
00:33:30,359 --> 00:33:31,279
I'm petty.

808
00:33:33,200 --> 00:33:35,359
I'll haunt both of you.

809
00:33:44,480 --> 00:33:46,119
Visit your grave?

810
00:33:46,720 --> 00:33:47,839
In your dreams.

811
00:33:48,359 --> 00:33:49,119
By then,

812
00:33:49,119 --> 00:33:50,119
I'll have forgotten you long ago.

813
00:33:50,480 --> 00:33:51,359
I'll never

814
00:33:51,359 --> 00:33:52,079
remember you again.

815
00:33:58,920 --> 00:33:59,519
Dadong.

816
00:34:00,519 --> 00:34:01,359
No matter what,

817
00:34:02,920 --> 00:34:03,759
show some fight.

818
00:34:05,359 --> 00:34:05,720
You...

819
00:34:06,960 --> 00:34:08,079
you have to survive.

820
00:34:09,960 --> 00:34:10,639
I'll wait for you.

821
00:34:34,719 --> 00:34:35,239
Okay.

822
00:34:39,480 --> 00:34:40,119
I'll keep it for now.

823
00:34:41,239 --> 00:34:42,039
When you're better,

824
00:34:43,320 --> 00:34:44,039
I'll put it back on you.

825
00:34:44,480 --> 00:34:44,960
Okay?

826
00:34:51,320 --> 00:34:52,400
Director Zhou. Dr. Fang.

827
00:34:53,079 --> 00:34:53,800
We're ready.

828
00:34:57,599 --> 00:34:59,159
Don't worry. Leave it to us.

829
00:35:28,239 --> 00:35:29,039
Release the tubing clamp.

830
00:35:33,920 --> 00:35:34,800
Start the centrifugal pump.

831
00:35:37,519 --> 00:35:39,159
Flow rate: three liters per minute.

832
00:36:12,199 --> 00:36:13,760
The greatest advantage

833
00:36:13,800 --> 00:36:14,880
of this artificial heart assist device

834
00:36:15,000 --> 00:36:16,239
is its small size and light weight.

835
00:36:16,320 --> 00:36:17,119
It's suitable for children.

836
00:36:17,400 --> 00:36:18,440
Its implantation method is advanced.

837
00:36:18,639 --> 00:36:19,639
While children wait

838
00:36:19,679 --> 00:36:20,679
for a heart transplant,

839
00:36:20,840 --> 00:36:21,440
it can help them

840
00:36:21,480 --> 00:36:22,480
resume normal activities.

841
00:36:22,880 --> 00:36:23,800
It may even

842
00:36:24,000 --> 00:36:25,000
replace heart transplantation.

843
00:36:25,719 --> 00:36:27,119
Is this a left ventricular assist device

844
00:36:27,159 --> 00:36:28,320
or a biventricular assist device?

845
00:36:28,639 --> 00:36:29,719
It's an LVAD.

846
00:36:31,440 --> 00:36:32,360
With current technology,

847
00:36:32,360 --> 00:36:33,320
do older children

848
00:36:33,320 --> 00:36:34,639
still have an advantage?

849
00:36:35,159 --> 00:36:35,920
That's one way to understand it.

850
00:36:36,079 --> 00:36:37,239
As children grow,

851
00:36:37,360 --> 00:36:38,280
there is more room

852
00:36:38,360 --> 00:36:39,320
inside the chest cavity.

853
00:36:39,719 --> 00:36:40,440
Their overall physical condition

854
00:36:40,760 --> 00:36:41,760
and tolerance

855
00:36:41,920 --> 00:36:42,920
are also better.

856
00:36:44,519 --> 00:36:46,480
Once this product launches,

857
00:36:46,559 --> 00:36:48,000
how much will it cost? Has a price been set?

858
00:36:48,599 --> 00:36:49,119
Not yet.

859
00:36:49,639 --> 00:36:51,039
But this is a premium model.

860
00:36:51,280 --> 00:36:52,400
It will cost at least a million yuan.

861
00:36:52,840 --> 00:36:53,480
That expensive?

862
00:36:54,920 --> 00:36:56,239
The R&D costs are high.

863
00:36:56,760 --> 00:36:57,440
A good product

864
00:36:57,639 --> 00:36:58,440
is worth the price.

865
00:37:02,760 --> 00:37:03,559
Director Zhou is here.

866
00:37:03,679 --> 00:37:04,599
Director Zhou. Director.

867
00:37:05,960 --> 00:37:06,400
Director.

868
00:37:08,039 --> 00:37:08,880
Isn't that Director Zhou?

869
00:37:09,039 --> 00:37:09,480
Yes.

870
00:37:11,079 --> 00:37:11,559
Director.

871
00:37:13,920 --> 00:37:14,840
While Lu Dadong is on ECMO,

872
00:37:14,880 --> 00:37:15,440
make sure

873
00:37:15,440 --> 00:37:16,119
you check on him often.

874
00:37:16,639 --> 00:37:17,079
Okay.

875
00:37:17,199 --> 00:37:17,920
I will.

876
00:37:19,079 --> 00:37:19,880
I'll start calling patients now.

877
00:37:20,880 --> 00:37:21,840
Notify Mai'anpei.

878
00:37:23,000 --> 00:37:23,880
Ask them to send someone else

879
00:37:23,920 --> 00:37:24,599
to handle our account.

880
00:37:27,000 --> 00:37:29,400
You want to replace Manager Ouyang?

881
00:37:31,480 --> 00:37:32,039
Is there a problem?

882
00:37:33,079 --> 00:37:34,760
No. No problem.

883
00:37:35,880 --> 00:37:36,480
Go notify them.

884
00:37:37,079 --> 00:37:37,679
Start calling patients.

885
00:37:38,320 --> 00:37:38,719
Okay.

886
00:37:44,440 --> 00:37:45,519
Hello, boss. What's wrong?

887
00:37:45,880 --> 00:37:46,760
Ouyang, where are you?

888
00:37:48,119 --> 00:37:49,239
I'm at the trade show.

889
00:37:49,960 --> 00:37:51,199
What did you do?

890
00:37:51,239 --> 00:37:52,199
Zhang Zhen called

891
00:37:52,239 --> 00:37:53,679
and said Zhou Xiaofeng wants you replaced.

892
00:37:53,880 --> 00:37:54,360
Replaced?

893
00:37:54,679 --> 00:37:55,440
Why?

894
00:37:56,239 --> 00:37:56,920
Why?

895
00:37:57,480 --> 00:37:58,679
How would I know?

896
00:37:59,239 --> 00:38:00,760
There must be some misunderstanding.

897
00:38:01,639 --> 00:38:02,480
Don't panic yet.

898
00:38:02,480 --> 00:38:03,800
I'll call Zhang Zhen right away.

899
00:38:04,280 --> 00:38:05,320
Please hurry, for heaven's sake.

900
00:38:05,639 --> 00:38:06,239
I know.

901
00:38:16,440 --> 00:38:17,519
All your follow-up results look good.

902
00:38:17,639 --> 00:38:18,280
The ECG and echocardiogram

903
00:38:18,320 --> 00:38:19,000
are both normal.

904
00:38:19,559 --> 00:38:20,239
Come back in three months

905
00:38:20,280 --> 00:38:20,960
for another checkup.

906
00:38:20,960 --> 00:38:21,599
Just get a Holter monitor test

907
00:38:21,679 --> 00:38:22,199
and a BNP test.

908
00:38:22,199 --> 00:38:22,719
That's all.

909
00:38:23,880 --> 00:38:25,119
Do I keep taking the medicine

910
00:38:25,119 --> 00:38:26,039
the same way as before?

911
00:38:26,519 --> 00:38:26,920
Yes.

912
00:38:27,280 --> 00:38:27,920
But during this time,

913
00:38:27,920 --> 00:38:29,119
if your chest tightness worsens

914
00:38:29,159 --> 00:38:30,480
or you wake up breathless at night,

915
00:38:30,639 --> 00:38:31,360
come back immediately.

916
00:38:32,400 --> 00:38:33,480
Okay. Thank you, Director Zhou.

917
00:38:33,800 --> 00:38:34,440
Thank you, Director Zhou.

918
00:38:39,679 --> 00:38:40,880
Dr. Zhang, what's going on?

919
00:38:40,960 --> 00:38:41,840
Is there some misunderstanding?

920
00:38:42,000 --> 00:38:42,679
Can you talk right now?

921
00:38:42,800 --> 00:38:43,599
Where is Director Zhou?

922
00:38:43,679 --> 00:38:44,159
I'll go find him.

923
00:38:44,159 --> 00:38:44,840
Outpatient clinic.

924
00:38:44,840 --> 00:38:45,400
Five o'clock.

925
00:38:47,239 --> 00:38:47,960
Hello, Xiao Ang.

926
00:38:48,400 --> 00:38:49,559
Navigate to Dongli Hospital.

927
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:50,639
Okay.

928
00:38:51,000 --> 00:38:53,079
Your route has been planned.

929
00:38:58,440 --> 00:38:59,599
I told you.

930
00:38:59,920 --> 00:39:01,599
It happened while I was tutoring my grandson.

931
00:39:01,760 --> 00:39:02,519
That's what caused it.

932
00:39:02,599 --> 00:39:03,119
Doctor,

933
00:39:03,960 --> 00:39:04,920
I personally feel

934
00:39:05,519 --> 00:39:06,400
fine.

935
00:39:07,039 --> 00:39:08,159
But the surgeon said

936
00:39:08,519 --> 00:39:09,199
they'd have to

937
00:39:10,079 --> 00:39:11,320
saw open my breastbone here.

938
00:39:11,519 --> 00:39:13,159
That sounds terrifying.

939
00:39:14,880 --> 00:39:15,519
But your arteries

940
00:39:15,519 --> 00:39:16,599
are severely narrowed.

941
00:39:16,760 --> 00:39:17,639
It's still quite dangerous.

942
00:39:17,880 --> 00:39:19,079
I suggest you be admitted immediately.

943
00:39:19,360 --> 00:39:20,159
I still need to be hospitalized?

944
00:39:20,920 --> 00:39:22,480
My grandson has an exam coming up.

945
00:39:23,719 --> 00:39:24,760
At a time like this,

946
00:39:25,079 --> 00:39:26,440
what matters more,

947
00:39:26,559 --> 00:39:27,760
Yangyang's exam or your life?

948
00:39:28,119 --> 00:39:29,199
Doctor, doctor, doctor.

949
00:39:29,440 --> 00:39:31,880
You haven't seen his grades.

950
00:39:32,159 --> 00:39:33,480
When his father and aunt were in school,

951
00:39:33,519 --> 00:39:34,559
when did either of them ever score

952
00:39:34,599 --> 00:39:36,039
39 on a subject?

953
00:39:36,519 --> 00:39:37,119
Sir.

954
00:39:37,920 --> 00:39:38,760
Given your current condition,

955
00:39:38,760 --> 00:39:39,480
I suggest you

956
00:39:39,480 --> 00:39:40,440
think more about yourself.

957
00:39:41,719 --> 00:39:43,159
May I ask, Doctor,

958
00:39:43,639 --> 00:39:46,079
will you be performing his surgery,

959
00:39:46,239 --> 00:39:47,079
or...

960
00:39:47,840 --> 00:39:48,840
Please wait a moment.

961
00:39:55,199 --> 00:39:55,840
Is everything ready?

962
00:39:55,840 --> 00:39:56,719
It's almost time.

963
00:39:57,599 --> 00:39:58,280
Wait for me.

964
00:39:58,320 --> 00:39:59,239
Let me change this.

965
00:39:59,639 --> 00:40:01,440
Stop waiting. The plane won't wait.

966
00:40:01,599 --> 00:40:02,880
I know. I know.

967
00:40:03,199 --> 00:40:03,679
One minute.

968
00:40:19,280 --> 00:40:19,679
Hello?

969
00:40:20,360 --> 00:40:21,599
I sent you a few photos.

970
00:40:21,800 --> 00:40:22,239
Take a look.

971
00:40:22,840 --> 00:40:23,440
I saw them.

972
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:25,000
I admitted a patient from clinic.

973
00:40:25,519 --> 00:40:26,519
A 70-year-old man.

974
00:40:26,960 --> 00:40:27,880
Severe three-vessel disease.

975
00:40:27,960 --> 00:40:28,920
Hypertension and diabetes.

976
00:40:29,239 --> 00:40:29,719
His condition is similar

977
00:40:29,760 --> 00:40:30,760
to Aunt Yang's back then.

978
00:40:31,599 --> 00:40:32,760
Has he contacted Cardiac Surgery?

979
00:40:33,840 --> 00:40:35,159
The patient refuses open-heart surgery.

980
00:40:35,320 --> 00:40:35,840
So I'm considering

981
00:40:35,840 --> 00:40:36,679
a hybrid procedure.

982
00:40:37,199 --> 00:40:37,679
That works.

983
00:40:37,840 --> 00:40:38,599
His condition is suitable for it.

984
00:40:39,880 --> 00:40:40,400
Is it urgent?

985
00:40:41,199 --> 00:40:42,400
Waiting until you return should be fine.

986
00:40:43,000 --> 00:40:43,880
Okay. No problem.

987
00:40:44,440 --> 00:40:44,920
We'll do it when I get back.

988
00:40:46,840 --> 00:40:48,280
Lin Xirui, are you done yet?

989
00:40:48,320 --> 00:40:48,920
Stop messing with that.

990
00:40:49,000 --> 00:40:49,880
Done, done, done.

991
00:40:50,199 --> 00:40:51,079
Hurry up.

992
00:40:52,800 --> 00:40:53,239
What are you doing?

993
00:40:53,719 --> 00:40:54,639
Are you going to Hainan to run a stall?

994
00:40:54,960 --> 00:40:56,000
I've spoken with Director Lin

995
00:40:56,039 --> 00:40:56,519
from Cardiac Surgery.

996
00:40:56,840 --> 00:40:57,519
He'll work with me

997
00:40:57,519 --> 00:40:58,239
to perform your surgery.

998
00:40:59,159 --> 00:41:00,039
When he returns from his trip,

999
00:41:00,119 --> 00:41:01,239
we'll finalize the surgical plan.

1000
00:41:01,400 --> 00:41:02,480
But we'll do our best to avoid

1001
00:41:02,559 --> 00:41:03,519
opening your entire chest.

1002
00:41:03,840 --> 00:41:04,719
That's wonderful.

1003
00:41:05,159 --> 00:41:06,320
That doesn't sound so scary anymore.

1004
00:41:06,400 --> 00:41:07,400
Maybe I'll even make it back

1005
00:41:07,480 --> 00:41:08,760
for my grandson's exam.

1006
00:41:09,239 --> 00:41:10,719
Thank you, Doctor. Thank you so much.

1007
00:41:11,400 --> 00:41:12,079
I never expected

1008
00:41:12,280 --> 00:41:13,119
things to be so convenient now.

1009
00:41:13,159 --> 00:41:14,400
The two departments just make a call

1010
00:41:14,760 --> 00:41:15,400
and everything is coordinated.

1011
00:41:15,440 --> 00:41:15,800
Yes.

1012
00:41:15,880 --> 00:41:16,760
This plan is great.

1013
00:41:16,760 --> 00:41:17,880
I feel much more at ease now.

1014
00:41:18,440 --> 00:41:19,000
Director.

1015
00:41:19,519 --> 00:41:21,159
Will Director Sheng...

1016
00:41:22,119 --> 00:41:22,599
It's fine.

1017
00:41:23,079 --> 00:41:24,280
Then I'll issue your admission order.

1018
00:41:25,079 --> 00:41:25,519
All right.

1019
00:41:25,559 --> 00:41:26,000
Okay.

1020
00:42:07,519 --> 00:42:07,880
Doctor.

1021
00:42:08,360 --> 00:42:09,559
Lately, I keep getting this feeling

1022
00:42:09,599 --> 00:42:10,360
like something suddenly

1023
00:42:10,360 --> 00:42:10,840
startles me.

1024
00:42:10,840 --> 00:42:11,760
It's like being frightened.

1025
00:42:11,960 --> 00:42:12,880
I'll just be sitting there normally,

1026
00:42:13,039 --> 00:42:13,840
then my heart suddenly drops.

1027
00:42:14,079 --> 00:42:15,199
It feels like I'm falling.

1028
00:42:15,239 --> 00:42:16,480
Like the weightless feeling

1029
00:42:16,639 --> 00:42:17,239
on a pirate ship ride

1030
00:42:17,239 --> 00:42:18,199
or when a plane hits turbulence?

1031
00:42:18,400 --> 00:42:19,039
Yes, yes. Exactly.

1032
00:42:21,800 --> 00:42:22,199
All right.

1033
00:42:24,239 --> 00:42:24,719
Thank you, Doctor.

1034
00:42:32,079 --> 00:42:32,519
Dr. Zhang.

1035
00:42:32,519 --> 00:42:33,599
I rushed back from the suburbs.

1036
00:42:33,599 --> 00:42:34,599
You seem busy today.

1037
00:42:35,199 --> 00:42:35,800
No, not at all.

1038
00:42:37,480 --> 00:42:38,239
How many patients are left?

1039
00:42:39,280 --> 00:42:39,840
Two.

1040
00:42:45,119 --> 00:42:45,639
Call the next one.

1041
00:42:55,840 --> 00:42:56,440
Director Zhou.

1042
00:42:57,159 --> 00:42:58,239
Do you have a moment to talk?
